[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_w3v8d")
reagent_id = "CaO"
title = "Calcium oxide"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]CaO[/cell]
[cell]Common name:[/cell][cell]Quicklime[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]56 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Solid[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reaction[/b]
2Ca + O₂ → 2CaO
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Basic oxide.
• Reacts strongly with water, producing calcium hydroxide.
• Reaction with water releases heat.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Production of cement and mortar.
• Used in steel production.
• Water treatment and soil improvement in agriculture.
[b]Safety[/b]
Corrosive and reacts with water, which can cause burns.
Dust can irritate the eyes and lungs."
